List Different types of database models

Different Types of Database Models

A database model defines how data is structured, stored, and related inside a database.

Here are the main types of database models:

1 Hierarchical Model

Data is organized in a tree-like structure

Each child has only one parent

One-to-many relationship

📌 Example use: Early banking systems
📌 Simple structure like folders in a computer

2 Network Model

Data is organized as a graph

A child can have multiple parents

Many-to-many relationships

📌 More flexible than hierarchical model

3 Relational Model (Most Popular)

Data stored in tables (rows & columns)

Uses primary keys and foreign keys

Uses SQL for operations

Examples of relational database systems:

MySQL

Oracle Database

Microsoft SQL Server

4 Entity-Relationship (ER) Model

Uses entities, attributes, and relationships

Represented using ER diagrams

Mainly used for database design

5 Object-Oriented Model

Data stored as objects

Supports inheritance, classes, and methods

Used in object-oriented programming environments

6 NoSQL Model

Non-relational databases

Stores data in flexible formats

Types of NoSQL models:

 Document Model

Example:

MongoDB

 Key-Value Model

Example:

Redis

 Column-Family Model

Example:

Apache Cassandra

 Graph Model

Example:

Neo4j

